{"tid":675021,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[QR關請入] EMV組織推QR Code付款認證計劃","createTime":"2018-05-23T07:55:59.000Z","updateTime":"2018-06-09T15:32:05.000Z","uid":1159,"like":1,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":6,"replies":[{"pid":"971fe6fe515e6161753912be915d3d0d67a77d2d","tid":675021,"uid":1159,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-05-23T07:55:59.000Z","msg":"<strong>EMVCo Creates QR Payment Mark to Help Promote Worldwide Acceptance and Interoperability of EMV&reg; QR Code Payments</strong><br />\n<br />\n21 May 2018 &ndash; EMVCo, the global technical body that manages the EMV&reg; Specifications, has created a QR Payment Mark to promote global interoperability across EMV QR Code payments. <strong>EMVCo has developed reproduction requirements and a free licensing structure to enable all implementers of EMV QR Code solutions to use the mark.</strong><br />\n<br />\nQR Codes are two-dimensional machine-readable barcodes, increasingly used to facilitate mobile payments at the point-of-sale. In 2017, EMVCo published the EMV&reg; QR Code Specifications to address two prevalent QR Code payment use-cases:<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Consumer-presented</strong> &ndash; the consumer displays the QR Code on their mobile device and the merchant uses an optical scanner to read the code.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Merchant-presented</strong> &ndash; the merchant displays the QR Code and the consumer uses their mobile device to scan the code.<br />\n<br />\nThe QR Payment Mark may be used to inform consumers that a merchant accepts EMV QR Code payment solutions. <strong>Supplemental messaging to consumers will confirm whether merchant-presented transactions, consumer-presented transactions, or both, are supported. The QR Payment Mark may also be used as an application indicator on a consumer mobile device when initiating a consumer-presented transaction. A royalty-free trademark license agreement and</strong> reproduction requirements are available in EMVCo&rsquo;s Trademark Centre.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;As momentum builds for leveraging emerging technologies, EMVCo is committed to facilitating worldwide acceptance and interoperability for EMV QR Code payments,&rdquo; comments Jack Pan, EMVCo Executive Committee Chair. &ldquo;The development of a uniform, recognisable QR Payment Mark that can be used on a royalty-free basis is an important step towards providing a universally consistent experience for both merchants and consumers.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://paymentsjournal.com/emvco-creates-qr-payment-mark-to-help-promote-worldwide-acceptance-and-interoperability-of-emv-qr-code-payments/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fpaymentsjournal.com%2Femvco-creates-qr-payment-mark-to-help-promote-worldwide-acceptance-and-interoperability-of-emv-qr-code-payments%2F&d=c%2BJMtgH2msu1T9K6ZL12a8PrXSGIZiPsBFv3mRhlVuk%3D&h=dac98fe2\" target=\"_blank\">http://paymentsjournal.com/emvco-creates-qr-payment-mark-to-help-promote-worldwide-acceptance-and-interoperability-of-emv-qr-code-payments/</a>"},{"pid":"1a173dc746e2ac830ec80c8a65ec23195c15f0c4","tid":675021,"uid":1159,"like":0,"dislike":3,"score":-3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-05-23T07:56:26.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://img.eservice-hk.net/upload/2018/04/17/125325_ea3dc39ca0b2f6b5f17abddec1f0e9a4.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimg.eservice-hk.net%2Fupload%2F2018%2F04%2F17%2F125325_ea3dc39ca0b2f6b5f17abddec1f0e9a4.png&h=c37f4f22&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"7da98b94d66f7769b3f00bba538bc855dccbc0a9","tid":675021,"uid":1159,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-05-23T15:35:13.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fbb8680cde16b92b8124bcd5e969dd9e246c721a","tid":675021,"uid":57705,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-05-23T15:49:07.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"e86561f2230647cdad51ebeaf7e95230a33b0e70","tid":675021,"uid":36445,"like":0,"d